# Component Patterns

## Project Stack
- **Next.js 16** App Router · **TypeScript** · **Tailwind CSS v3** · **shadcn/ui** primitives
- Path alias: `@/*` → `src/*`

## Section Structure
Every landing page section follows this pattern:
```tsx
<section id="section-id" className="section-padding">
  <div className="container-max">
    {/* Section header */}
    <div className="text-center mb-16">
      <Badge variant="subtle" className="mb-4">Label</Badge>
      <h2 className="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
        Plain text <span className="gradient-text">gradient highlight</span>
      </h2>
      <p className="text-lg text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Supporting copy here.
      </p>
    </div>
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
</section>
```

## Cards / Surfaces
Always use glass-style cards — never solid white:
```tsx
// ✅ Standard card
<div className="bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm border border-black/10 rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow" />

// ✅ Featured / highlighted card
<div className="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm border border-primary shadow-xl shadow-primary/10 rounded-2xl p-8" />
```

## Buttons
Uses `src/components/ui/button.tsx` with CVA variants:
- `variant="gradient"` → primary CTA (blue→violet gradient)
- `variant="outline"` → secondary action
- `variant="ghost"` → nav/inline actions
- `size="xl"` → hero CTAs · `size="lg"` → section CTAs · `size="sm"` → nav

## Badge
Uses `src/components/ui/badge.tsx`:
- `variant="subtle"` → section labels (blue tint)
- `variant="gradient"` → highlighted badges (e.g. "Most Popular")

## File Locations
```
src/
  app/           → layout.tsx, page.tsx, globals.css
  components/
    layout/      → Navbar.tsx, Footer.tsx
    sections/    → Hero, LogoBar, Features, HowItWorks, Pricing, Testimonials, FAQ, CTA
    ui/          → button.tsx, badge.tsx (shadcn primitives)
  lib/
    utils.ts     → cn() helper
```

## cn() Helper
Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge Tailwind classes conditionally:
```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
className={cn("base-class", condition && "conditional-class", className)}
```
